---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us | Save Editor Online"
  description="Learn about the team behind Save Editor Online - the free, secure, browser-based game save editing tool trusted by gamers worldwide."
>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-6xl">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
        About Save Editor Online
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Empowering gamers with the freedom to play their way. The world's most trusted, secure, and
        universal browser-based save file editor.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-16">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 text-center"
      >
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary-600 mb-2">100%</div>
        <div class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-medium">Client-Side Privacy</div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 text-center"
      >
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary-600 mb-2">50+</div>
        <div class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-medium">Supported Formats</div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 text-center"
      >
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary-600 mb-2">Free</div>
        <div class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-medium">Forever Open</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-blue max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Save Editor Online was created with a simple but powerful goal: <strong
            >to democratize game modification</strong
          >. We believe that single-player gaming is a personal experience. Whether you want to skip
          a tedious grind, recover a corrupted save file, or experiment with different story paths,
          you should have the tools to do so easily and safely.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4">
          In the past, editing save files required downloading sketchy software, hex editing, or
          complex technical knowledge. We changed that by building a powerful, universal editor that
          runs directly in your web browser. No downloads, no installations, no risk.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Why Trust Us?</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">üîí Client-Side Technology</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
              Security is our top priority. Unlike other tools, <strong
                >Save Editor Online processes everything locally on your device</strong
              >. When you "upload" a file, it never actually leaves your computer. It is loaded into
              your browser's memory, edited, and saved back to your disk. We never see, store, or
              transmit your game data.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">üõ°Ô∏è Transparent & Safe</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
              We are committed to transparency. Our tool is built on modern web standards (HTML5,
              WebAssembly) and is regularly updated to ensure compatibility and safety. We strictly
              oppose cheating in multiplayer games and design our tools solely for single-player
              experiences.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Supported Technologies</h2>
        <p class="mb-6">
          We are constantly expanding our support for game engines and file formats. Our current
          capabilities include:
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg"
          >
            <span class="text-2xl">üéÆ</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-bold">RPG Maker</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">.rpgsave (MV/MZ)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg"
          >
            <span class="text-2xl">üé≤</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-bold">Unity</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">PlayerPrefs, JSON</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg"
          >
            <span class="text-2xl">‚ö°</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-bold">Unreal Engine</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">.sav (GVAS)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg"
          >
            <span class="text-2xl">üé≠</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-bold">Ren'Py</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">.save (Viewer)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg"
          >
            <span class="text-2xl">üëæ</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-bold">GameMaker</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">.ini, .json</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg"
          >
            <span class="text-2xl">üìù</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-bold">NaniNovel</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">.nson</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details
            class="group bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer"
          >
            <summary class="font-bold text-lg flex justify-between items-center list-none">
              <span>Is Save Editor Online really free?</span>
              <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
                <svg
                  fill="none"
                  height="24"
                  shape-rendering="geometricPrecision"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg
                >
              </span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
              Yes, 100% free with no hidden costs. We are ad-supported which allows us to keep the
              service free for everyone.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details
            class="group bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer"
          >
            <summary class="font-bold text-lg flex justify-between items-center list-none">
              <span>Is my data safe?</span>
              <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
                <svg
                  fill="none"
                  height="24"
                  shape-rendering="geometricPrecision"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg
                >
              </span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
              Absolutely. All file processing happens in your browser. Your save files are never
              uploaded to our servers.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details
            class="group bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer"
          >
            <summary class="font-bold text-lg flex justify-between items-center list-none">
              <span>Will using this tool get me banned?</span>
              <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
                <svg
                  fill="none"
                  height="24"
                  shape-rendering="geometricPrecision"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg
                >
              </span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
              For single-player games, no. We do not support or encourage cheating in online or
              multiplayer games.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details
            class="group bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer"
          >
            <summary class="font-bold text-lg flex justify-between items-center list-none">
              <span>Can you add support for a specific game?</span>
              <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
                <svg
                  fill="none"
                  height="24"
                  shape-rendering="geometricPrecision"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg
                >
              </span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
              Let us know via our contact form! We prioritize based on user demand and technical
              feasibility.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
  [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Save Editor Online",
      "url": "https://saveeditor.online",
      "logo": "https://saveeditor.online/favicon.svg",
      "sameAs": ["https://twitter.com/SaveEditorOnline"],
      "contactPoint": {
        "@type": "ContactPoint",
        "email": "support@saveeditor.com",
        "contactType": "customer support"
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Save Editor Online really free?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, 100% free with no hidden costs. We are ad-supported which allows us to keep the service free for everyone."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is my data safe?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Absolutely. All file processing happens in your browser. Your save files are never uploaded to our servers."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Will using this tool get me banned?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "For single-player games, no. We do not support or encourage cheating in online or multiplayer games."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can you add support for a specific game?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Let us know via our contact form! We prioritize based on user demand and technical feasibility."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
</script>
